She flipped to a blank page and wrote the date on it. Then, she wrote below the date: "5/11/648-12/13/648".
"Are you reflecting on past events?" Avery asked, looking at the old notebook. Carly nodded. "Do you think they'll let you out for Christmas? There are only a few days left until Christmas."
Carly knocked twice on the lantern, indicating "no". Avery wasn't surprised. The Ice King never allowed Carly to leave because, in his eyes, Carly was "a flaw". Carly was born deaf, and she was the only girl in the family, with all the other children being boys.
Avery was similar, in a unique way. When Avery publicly revealed their non-binary identity, the world seemed to change. As a punishment for being different, Avery was assigned to work alone for most of the time.
Avery was also forced to be a princess's servant. However, Avery didn't mind because Avery had a friend.
"Your birthday is coming up, isn't it?" Avery asked, remembering that the princess's birthday was in a few days. Carly nodded, and a faint sadness flickered in her pale blue eyes.
"Do you want to celebrate?" Avery asked, recalling how Carly had answered this question last time.
No. Carly tapped her fingers on the table. Avery knew this was a difficult topic for Carly. It was on this day that she was imprisoned in this room, while her mother was executed. Avery was just an infant at the time, but Avery remembered the anger of the servants and citizens. Avery had heard that Queen Elwynn was a good queen and could magically predict future events.
"So... what do you want to do?" Avery asked. Carly looked up at Avery, her eyes shining with excitement. She handed Avery a piece of paper. However, when Avery looked down at it...
6 inches X 6 inches canvas
White, shades of blue paint
6 different sizes of brushes
Easel
“Do you want me to get those for you?” Avery turned to the silent princess, who kept tapping away, her ponytail bobbing back and forth. “Right?” When TA saw the normally quiet princess so enthusiastic about something, they couldn't help but laugh. This was the first time she wanted something outside the room, and it wasn't related to books.
“Okay! See you later?” Avery said, standing up and walking through the messy papers and notebooks.
Carly nodded and continued to retreat into the thick blanket, reflecting on her memories.
Avery walked out of the room, feeling hopeful that the princess was finally willing to try new things and had even made some requests that were beyond her abilities (such as paints).
Avery walked through the hall again, trying not to pay attention to the servants' whispered conversations.
“I heard she was possessed by Queen Elwynn, so she always goes to that room.”
“I heard she eats children in that room.”
“Is it normal for her to look like a man?”
Avery couldn't take these words anymore, so they covered their ears. Avery went to the room of the royal artist, which was located in the east wing, left of the second door.
Avery arrived at the door, which was just like Carly's door, beautifully decorated. The door had a white dragon painted on it, one of the six original dragons that created the Frost Kingdom. It wasn't surprising that the artist liked history and painted the white dragon on the door.
Avery opened the door, expecting everything to be the same. There were paints, pencils, and papers scattered all over the place, and easels covered every inch of the wall. However, the scene inside the room was completely different. The room was clean, and there was a red velvet backdrop and a stool in the corner. The heir to the throne, Aquilo, was sitting on the stool, painting a portrait.
“Good morning, Avery! Want to see your future king's portrait?” Aquilo asked, winking at Avery.
"Sorry, Prince," Avery replied, starting to look around for the things the princess wanted. "I just came to get some art supplies."
"Little one, don't leave so soon?" Prince Aquaro asked, "But I want to see you!"
"I don't want to," Avery found the art supplies on the list and put them in a box. "And I'm not a girl either."
The prince didn't take it seriously. "Oh, sweetie, this is just a phase! You'll get over it when you grow up!" he said vaguely.
"I have to go," Avery said, feeling uneasy because the prince kept talking. Avery remembered all the negative comments people made about Avery's gender identity. I really want to get away from him.
"Are you leaving so soon?" The prince suddenly appeared at the door, ignoring the royal artist's call.
"This is not the behavior a future king should have!" TA shouted loudly.
"No one will know. People won't believe you, and if that artist still values his life, he won't say anything either." The prince turned around to look at the artist, then leaned in close to Avery. "How about a date?" Avery shivered with fear. Of course, Avery had heard many threats before, but they all came from someone other than the prince, let alone this future king.
"Do you know what the word 'no' means?" TA snapped, pushing the prince away.
"No." Arquero laughed, answering. This prince who could get whatever he wanted certainly didn't know what the word 'no' meant.
Avery rolled his eyes. "Why so many people, and you want to go out with me? How many suitors do you have? Five hundred?"
He smiled, interrupting, "Actually, it's over five hundred." He shook his hair in the cold wind.
"See! Why me? I'm a nuisance in the palace." Avery crossed his arms.
"You're the most beautiful girl I've ever seen." Aquilo placed his finger on Avery's chin, forcing Avery to look up at him.
